        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As the reigning triple World Touring Car Champions, Cyan Racing is taking a victory lap by giving the enthusiast community the Volvo P1800 ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "restomod we certainly deserve",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/tyler-hoover-sings-praises-for-restomods/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". We love some good restomod ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "American muscle cars",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/motorweeks-retro-review-muscle/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", as do quite a few of the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Swedes",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/swedish-mopar-collection/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " by the way, but something unexpected and well-executed like this is a welcome treat. After all, most people don’t associate Volvo with a need for speed, especially now the Swedish automaker is looking to kill such bad habits. But that doesn’t mean you can’t have fun in a classic Volvo and the P1800 has the right looks for just such a project.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/09/Motorious--42.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Cyan Racing"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cyan Racing decided to resurrect the 60s Volvo sports car in part because the company was created to race Volvos in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Sweden",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/swedish-mopar-collection/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". In fact, these are the guys who started Polestar before it was bought out by Volvo. To celebrate the heritage of the only mass-produced car brand left in Sweden, Cyan Racing settled on one of the sexiest-looking Volvos ever created.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "To start off, this car has absolutely ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "no driver’s aids",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/articles/news/dodge-challenger-crashed/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". For some that’ll be terrifying and for others that’s music to their ears. This means no ABS or brake booster, so you’re really getting that pure experience.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However, there is a long list of changes. For starters, the track is wider and the 18-inch forged wheels are larger that the originals. They’re also wrapped with Pirelli P Zero tires for the right kind of grip.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/09/Motorious---1--20.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Cyan Racing"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Of course, the engine has been upgraded to a 2.0-liter turbo four-cylinder based on the one used in the Volvo S60 TCI race car. It pushes an amazing 420-horsepower and redlines at 7700 rpm. Bolted up to it is a 5-speed custom Holinger transmission which Cyan Racing says mimics the car’s original mechanical feel.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Carbon-fiber and high-strength steel reinforcements have been added to the chassis to compensate for that huge power bump. This is still a rear-wheel-drive car, but the factory live axle has been swapped with an independent rear setup Cyan designed. A torque-biased rear limited-slip differential has also been installed. Both the front and rear suspension is fully adjustable.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This car sounds appropriately amazing, but production will be limited and pricing starts at $500,000. Now that they’re done a P1800 restomod, we think Cyan Racing should do a Volvo 240 next and call it the Flying Brick.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      }
    ],
    "direction": "ltr",
